🦄 Dropping some color on your feed. .
I took a few days off to get my mind right, and I strongly suggest if you also need one please take it. The shit will be here when you get back & hopefully the time away will give you the recharge & clarity that you need. Feeling like u have to keep up with the latest news, hottest tea, makeup releases & politics...on top of living your real life can be exhausting. I’m reminding myself that I did what I could with each day and there’s no reason to dwell on what I could have done better, or how I could more efficiently manage my time. It’s done & I’ll try to do better the next day. Now let’s get it this week. Happy Sunday fam 😛😘

If you had asked me a year ago if I’d be standing on a #NYFW runway completely bare faced ready to strut my stuff, I’d probably laugh. But that’s my favorite thing about life. It’s completely unpredictable and usually turns out even more fabulous than you could have ever dreamed of. Thank you @olay for a once in a lifetime experience. I’ve discovered some new products, met phenomenal women from different walks of life and focused on loving myself a little better. I’ll say this challenge was definitely a success. ❤️ [ad]

Blue Hair Energy 😛💙
.
There is a full review of this product now on YT. (Link in bio)
•Hair Color: @hairpaintwax Blue + White (highlights)
I’m always looking for ways to switch up my look with little to no damage to my natural hair. I’ve been wanting blue hair since high school, so I’m living my ENTIRE life with this color. I even slept in a shower cap to preserve the hair for one more day 😂. I love the vibrancy & how easy the application was. Could have lived without the excessive flakiness. But it wasn’t a deal breaker because bouncing around town with my blue fro was totally worth it. Would you guys try this product?

I’m ready for my closeup y’all 😛. Morning routines has never been easier. Going into this 28 Day Challenge I didn’t really know what to expect or how my sensitive skin would respond. I religiously used the @olay Regenerist Whip every morning as a moisturizer/sunscreen for barefaced days or even underneath my makeup. My skin just feels healthy and has this bounce to it. I’ve noticed slightly smoother skin & it’s also improved the overall firmness as well 🙌🏽. Tomorrow I’ll be hitting the runway at NYFW with a group of phenomenal women all barefaced & bold. Can’t wait to share with you guys. [Ad]

Day 14 Check-in. Look. Everyone has their thing. My skin has been something that I have been struggling with for a long time. I’ve tried every product under the sun to clear up my skin and it’s getting better, little by little. It’s something that I think a lot of people struggle with, but don’t talk about enough. In a little less than 3 weeks I will be walking in a NYFW Show with @olay baring the skin I’m in. No makeup. Just me and the runway. This is probably one of my proudest moments ever. Proving that imperfect skin is just as beautiful. I love you guys so much & thank you from the bottom of my heart. None of this would be possible without the support of each and every one of you. ❤️
.
SN/Swipe: The left photo was taken a few months back. Just wanted to show a process pic along the way. For the last 14 days, I’ve been maintaining how far my skin has come by using the @olay Daily Facials wipes to remove my makeup and start my days cleansed. In addition I’m using the Ultimate Eye Cream to hydrate & brighten my under eyes. 🙌🏽
